00:10:35,416 --> 00:10:37,708
you're probably bad at cleaning
and laundry, right, Rem-rin?

254
00:10:37,791 --> 00:10:39,041
- On the contrary,

255
00:10:39,125 --> 00:10:41,291
I'm generally good
at all household tasks.

256
00:10:41,375 --> 00:10:43,750
I'm also better at cleaning
and laundry than my sister.

257
00:10:43,833 --> 00:10:44,875
- Seriously?

258
00:10:44,958 --> 00:10:46,291
Does your sister
even have a purpose?

259
00:10:46,375 --> 00:10:49,583
- You are truly
a unique young man.

260
00:10:49,666 --> 00:10:52,166
You come to the mansion
of Margrave Mathers

261
00:10:52,250 --> 00:10:53,708
in the kingdom of Lugunica

262
00:10:53,791 --> 00:10:56,375
and you say you
don't understand a thing.

263
00:10:56,458 --> 00:10:57,791
- So what do you mean by that?

264
00:10:57,875 --> 00:10:59,416
Is something bad happening
in this country?

265
00:10:59,500 --> 00:11:02,708
- Well, it is not in
an agreeable state,

266
00:11:02,791 --> 00:11:04,083
which only makes sense.

267
00:11:04,166 --> 00:11:07,541
After all,
Lugunica doesn't have a king.

268
00:11:07,625 --> 00:11:09,416
Now, don't look so alarmed.

269
00:11:09,500 --> 00:11:11,166
There's no need to be concerned.

270
00:11:11,250 --> 00:11:13,750
Everyone in this country
is already quite aware

271
00:11:13,833 --> 00:11:15,833
of that circumstance being
their reality.

272
00:11:15,916 --> 00:11:17,125
- Wow, really?

273
00:11:17,208 --> 00:11:19,208
I expected a,
"Now that you know my secret,

274
00:11:19,291 --> 00:11:20,833
I can't let you leave
here alive" thing.

275
00:11:20,916 --> 00:11:23,916
- Roughly around the same time
the king went into hiding,

276
00:11:24,000 --> 00:11:26,750
an epidemic began to spread
throughout the castle.

277
00:11:26,833 --> 00:11:29,333
The king and his children
are the last of his line.

278
00:11:29,416 --> 00:11:31,458
At this moment,
the nation is being managed

279
00:11:31,541 --> 00:11:34,625
by a council of wise men
and that council is currently

280
00:11:34,708 --> 00:11:36,458
in the process
of selecting a new king.

281
00:11:36,541 --> 00:11:39,500
- Okay, think I'm starting
to get the picture now.

282
00:11:39,583 --> 00:11:41,250
On top of the king's absence,

283
00:11:41,333 --> 00:11:43,000
the royal selection
is causing confusion

284
00:11:43,083 --> 00:11:44,166
in the kingdom.

285
00:11:44,250 --> 00:11:45,666
Suddenly I appear
from another country--

286
00:11:45,750 --> 00:11:47,375
wait, I'm totally suspect here!

287
00:11:47,458 --> 00:11:49,000
- And on top of that,

288
00:11:49,083 --> 00:11:50,625
you made contact
with Miss Emilia,

289
00:11:50,708 --> 00:11:52,458
thus initiating
a direct connection

290
00:11:52,541 --> 00:11:54,750
to my household.
Ah, the dilemma.

291
00:11:54,833 --> 00:11:56,833
- Mm?
Hey, hold on a second.

292
00:11:56,916 --> 00:11:57,958
Why would the lord
of the mansion

293
00:11:58,041 --> 00:11:59,291
call her Miss Emilia?

294
00:11:59,375 --> 00:12:01,583
- I'm not sure how things are
where you're from,

295
00:12:01,666 --> 00:12:05,166
but here we address those
with higher status respectfully.

296
00:12:05,250 --> 00:12:06,708
- [grunts]
But, uh,

297
00:12:06,791 --> 00:12:09,208
that would mean Mili here is,
uh--

298
00:12:09,291 --> 00:12:13,625
- Officially, my current title
is candidate for the 42nd ruler

299
00:12:13,708 --> 00:12:15,541
of the Kingdom of Lugunica,

300
00:12:15,625 --> 00:12:18,625
with the backing of the honor
of Lord Margrave Roswaal.

301
00:12:18,708 --> 00:12:19,958
- What?

302
00:12:20,041 --> 00:12:21,625
- Sorry to surprise you
like that.

303
00:12:21,708 --> 00:12:24,041
I wasn't trying to keep it
a secret or anything.

304
00:12:24,125 --> 00:12:25,750
<i>[exciting music]</i>

305
00:12:25,833 --> 00:12:27,708
- Hey, it's that insignia.

306
00:12:27,791 --> 00:12:30,750
- This qualifies one
to be a candidate for king.

307
00:12:30,833 --> 00:12:33,625
It's a ceremonial touch stone
that's used to determine

308
00:12:33,708 --> 00:12:35,291
if one is worthy to sit
at the throne

309
00:12:35,375 --> 00:12:36,875
and lead this country
as a monarch.

310
00:12:36,958 --> 00:12:38,083
- Wait a second.

311
00:12:38,166 --> 00:12:39,458
Are you saying you lost
an insignia

312
00:12:39,541 --> 00:12:41,666
that qualifies you
to rule the kingdom?

313
00:12:41,750 --> 00:12:43,791
- Now, don't put it like that!
I didn't lose it!

314
00:12:43,875 --> 00:12:45,291
It was stolen from me
by a thief!

315
00:12:45,375 --> 00:12:47,000
- That's the same thing!

316
00:12:47,083 --> 00:12:49,625
And what happens if you manage
to lose that thing, anyway?

317
00:12:49,708 --> 00:12:51,625
Will a government office
issue another one?

318
00:12:51,708 --> 00:12:54,000
- Oh, what a dreadful scenario.
[both grunting]

319
00:12:54,083 --> 00:12:56,208
If you'd lost it then there
would be no doubt.

320
00:12:56,291 --> 00:12:58,458
The belief would be that one
who can't even protect

321
00:12:58,541 --> 00:13:01,166
a tiny insignia has no business
being entrusted

322
00:13:01,250 --> 00:13:03,541
with the nation's rule,
and that would be the end.

323
00:13:03,625 --> 00:13:05,166
- Well, knowing those facts,

324
00:13:05,250 --> 00:13:06,791
I'd say I did a damn good job,

325
00:13:06,875 --> 00:13:09,000
and it totally raises
my expectations

326
00:13:09,083 --> 00:13:10,041
for a nice reward.

327
00:13:10,125 --> 00:13:11,666
- Yeah, you're right about that.

328
00:13:11,750 --> 00:13:14,208
You're a true savior to me
and I'm very thankful.

329
00:13:14,291 --> 00:13:15,500
So ask me for anything.

330
00:13:15,583 --> 00:13:17,500
- Yes, you heard the lady.

331
00:13:17,583 --> 00:13:20,375
Any reward you desire.
Just name it.

332
00:13:20,458 --> 00:13:22,416
- [laughs]

333
00:13:22,500 --> 00:13:24,750
Well, in that case,
I have but one request.

334
00:13:24,833 --> 00:13:25,958
- [giggles]

335
00:13:26,041 --> 00:13:28,041
<i>♪ ♪</i>

336
00:13:28,125 --> 00:13:29,916
I'm starting
to like this mansion.

337
00:13:30,000 --> 00:13:31,708
Hire me to work here.

338
00:13:34,375 --> 00:13:35,416
- [sneezes]

339
00:13:37,458 --> 00:13:39,375
- No, that's not quite right.

340
00:13:39,458 --> 00:13:41,833
Wasn't there anything else
that fit, Subaru?

341
00:13:41,916 --> 00:13:44,291
- Oddly, some of the girls'
stuff fit me, but--

342
00:13:44,375 --> 00:13:46,833
- Our deepest apologies
on the wardrobe, sir--

343
00:13:46,916 --> 00:13:48,333
I mean, Subaru.
- I must say,

344
00:13:48,416 --> 00:13:51,000
you look utterly ridiculous,
sir--I mean, Barusu.

345
00:13:51,083 --> 00:13:52,291
- Oh, good job, Ram.

346
00:13:52,375 --> 00:13:54,625
You just turned my name
into a blinding curse.

347
00:13:54,708 --> 00:13:57,875
- Rem, notice anything about
Barusu's ludicrous appearance?

348
00:13:57,958 --> 00:13:59,833
- Well, the shoulders
fit him funny,

349
00:13:59,916 --> 00:14:02,041
his legs are short,
and his eyes are scary.

350
00:14:02,125 --> 00:14:05,083
- Two of those are things
I can't do anything about, okay?

351
00:14:05,166 --> 00:14:06,458
- We can't allow you
to work here

352
00:14:06,541 --> 00:14:08,083
in such shoddy-looking attire.

353
00:14:08,166 --> 00:14:10,583
People would begin to question
Lord Roswaal's dignity.

354
00:14:10,666 --> 00:14:13,000
Let us alter the jacket
at the very least.

355
00:14:13,083 --> 00:14:14,583
Rem, if you wouldn't mind.
- [chuckles]

356
00:14:14,666 --> 00:14:15,708
If you'll excuse me,

357
00:14:15,791 --> 00:14:17,500
I have to study
for the royal selection.

358
00:14:17,583 --> 00:14:19,083
Good luck with your work,
Subaru.

359
00:14:19,166 --> 00:14:22,000
- Yep, leave it to me, Mili.
[grunts]

360
00:14:22,083 --> 00:14:24,000
- I'll take your measurements
for the fitting,

361
00:14:24,083 --> 00:14:26,125
so stand still
with your back straight.

362
00:14:26,208 --> 00:14:27,750
- [grunts]

363
00:14:27,833 --> 00:14:28,875
[gasps]

364
00:14:28,958 --> 00:14:30,291
- Please don't make
strange noises

365
00:14:30,375 --> 00:14:32,375
during this process.
It's unpleasant for me.

366
00:14:32,458 --> 00:14:35,083
- Unpleasant for you?
And that was beyond my control!

367
00:14:35,166 --> 00:14:36,625
This is awkward for a guy,
you know?

368
00:14:36,708 --> 00:14:38,375
- This is the V.I.P. room.

369
00:14:38,458 --> 00:14:39,833
This is the bathing room.

370
00:14:39,916 --> 00:14:41,208
This is the kitchen.

371
00:14:41,291 --> 00:14:42,958
And this is the lavatory.

372
00:14:43,041 --> 00:14:44,208
- In a mansion like this,

373
00:14:44,291 --> 00:14:45,916
I bet the restroom
is freaking huge.

374
00:14:46,000 --> 00:14:47,625
- My sweet Bubby.

375
00:14:47,708 --> 00:14:49,500
Oh, oh, I love your fur.
- [laughing]

376
00:14:49,583 --> 00:14:51,458
- [groans]
- Don't worry.

377
00:14:51,541 --> 00:14:52,958
I won't tell a soul about this.

378
00:14:53,041 --> 00:14:54,375
The feel of that fur
would make anyo--

379
00:14:54,458 --> 00:14:55,708
[screams]

380
00:14:55,791 --> 00:14:58,541
Ow, come on, now!
Let me finish, you little--

381
00:14:58,625 --> 00:14:59,500
[grunts]

382
00:14:59,583 --> 00:15:00,500
[gasps]

383
00:15:00,583 --> 00:15:01,791
- You just witnessed

384
00:15:01,875 --> 00:15:04,041
Miss Beatrice's door crossing.
- Oh, really?

385
00:15:04,125 --> 00:15:06,250
So it's a spell that can connect
any door in the mansion

386
00:15:06,333 --> 00:15:07,791
to her own room.
Is that it?

387
00:15:07,875 --> 00:15:10,458
- And once Miss Beatrice
has eliminated her presence,

388
00:15:10,541 --> 00:15:13,666
there's no way to find her
without trying every door.

389
00:15:15,375 --> 00:15:17,166
- She's in here!
- [screams]

390
00:15:17,250 --> 00:15:19,041
- Impressive, Subaru.

391
00:15:19,125 --> 00:15:21,125
- All right, how did you pick
the right door again?

392
00:15:21,208 --> 00:15:22,625
- Like I told you before,
remember?

393
00:15:22,708 --> 00:15:25,250
I'm a flag crusher
who makes game masters cry.

394
00:15:25,333 --> 00:15:26,958
- I have no idea
what you're talking about.

395
00:15:27,041 --> 00:15:29,458
- Tell me, how do you fit in
around here, anyway?

396
00:15:29,541 --> 00:15:30,916
You Roswaal's little sister?

397
00:15:31,000 --> 00:15:33,791
- I would never want to be
his sister, I suppose.

398
00:15:33,875 --> 00:15:35,666
- Betty's a librarian
who oversees

399
00:15:35,750 --> 00:15:37,625
the Roswaal Mansion's
forbidden library.

400
00:15:37,708 --> 00:15:40,916
- Master Roswaal is the greatest
magic user in the kingdom.

401
00:15:41,000 --> 00:15:43,291
He has many books
that mustn't be seen by others,

402
00:15:43,375 --> 00:15:45,166
and Miss Beatrice
has been contracted

403
00:15:45,250 --> 00:15:46,625
to protect them
from prying eyes.

404
00:15:46,708 --> 00:15:48,916
- Understand now?
Then go away!

405
00:15:50,875 --> 00:15:53,208
- This concludes our tour
of the mansion.

406
00:15:53,583 --> 00:15:55,375
So do you have any questions?

407
00:15:55,458 --> 00:15:57,833
- I know there's no use
saying this after it's over,

408
00:15:57,916 --> 00:16:00,208
but don't you think it would
have made a whole lot more sense

409
00:16:00,291 --> 00:16:03,041
for Mili to take me around
for the tour event?

410
00:16:03,125 --> 00:16:04,333
- If you have no questions,

411
00:16:04,416 --> 00:16:06,791
then let's get to the ins
and outs of your job.

412
00:16:06,875 --> 00:16:09,208
Basically, you'll be helping
with my work, Barusu.

413
00:16:09,291 --> 00:16:11,666
- This must be the moment when
my hidden skills as a butler

414
00:16:11,750 --> 00:16:13,208
finally reveal themselves.

415
00:16:13,291 --> 00:16:14,416
- My work today consists

416
00:16:14,500 --> 00:16:15,750
of caring for the front yard
and garden,

417
00:16:15,833 --> 00:16:17,583
helping to prepare lunch,
polishing the silver,

418
00:16:17,666 --> 00:16:19,166
airing out the futons,
doing the laundry,

419
00:16:19,250 --> 00:16:20,291
cleaning the bathrooms,

420
00:16:20,375 --> 00:16:21,791
and the mansion's monthly
soot cleaning.

421
00:16:21,875 --> 00:16:23,750
[distant church bells ringing]

422
00:16:23,833 --> 00:16:26,416
- [groans]
Oh, finally.

423
00:16:26,500 --> 00:16:27,833
[knocking]
[grunts]

424
00:16:27,916 --> 00:16:28,875
<i>- This is Rem.</i>

425
00:16:28,958 --> 00:16:30,333
<i>Do you have a moment, Subaru?</i>

426
00:16:30,416 --> 00:16:31,875
- Sure, yeah, I'm good.

427
00:16:31,958 --> 00:16:34,000
I won't do anything weird
so come on in.

428
00:16:34,083 --> 00:16:37,041
<i>- Your permission makes</i>
<i>you sound less credible.</i>

429
00:16:37,125 --> 00:16:38,416
<i>Pardon me.</i>

430
00:16:40,041 --> 00:16:41,791
- You already finished
the alterations?

431
00:16:41,875 --> 00:16:43,625
- When it's
Lord Roswaal's clothing,

432
00:16:43,708 --> 00:16:46,625
I must be careful and precise,
but since this is yours--

433
00:16:46,708 --> 00:16:48,583
- Wait, you cut corners
'cause it's me?

434
00:16:48,666 --> 00:16:50,708
<i>[quirky music]</i>

435
00:16:50,791 --> 00:16:52,916
I hate to admit it,
but it's perfect.

436
00:16:53,000 --> 00:16:54,916
How do I look?
Good, huh?

437
00:16:55,000 --> 00:16:56,958
- With this outfit over
the bizarre attire

438
00:16:57,041 --> 00:16:58,250
that you were
originally wearing,

439
00:16:58,333 --> 00:17:00,666
no one in any strange garment
could rival you.

440
00:17:00,750 --> 00:17:02,041
- Not a compliment at all.

441
00:17:02,125 --> 00:17:03,666
- And what shall
we do with those?

442
00:17:03,750 --> 00:17:05,125
- This one's easy.

443
00:17:05,208 --> 00:17:06,416
Got a needle and thread?

444
00:17:06,500 --> 00:17:07,750
- Yes, I brought them.

445
00:17:07,833 --> 00:17:09,708
Would you like me to repair them
for you now?

446
00:17:09,791 --> 00:17:11,333
- Nah, that'll be okay.
I can do it.

447
00:17:11,416 --> 00:17:14,208
Don't underestimate
my sewing skills.

448
00:17:14,291 --> 00:17:17,791
[humming]

449
00:17:17,875 --> 00:17:19,416
- I'm honestly surprised.

450
00:17:19,500 --> 00:17:22,333
I must give you full marks
for your sewing.

451
00:17:22,416 --> 00:17:24,625
I'd like to add, however,
that much like you,

452
00:17:24,708 --> 00:17:27,458
it doesn't appear
useful whatsoever.

453
00:17:27,833 --> 00:17:29,083
[stabbing]
<i>- Ow!</i>

454
00:17:29,166 --> 00:17:30,583
[screaming]
- You may get full marks

455
00:17:30,666 --> 00:17:33,416
for sewing but you're still
useless with a knife, Barusu.

456
00:17:33,500 --> 00:17:35,791
- As always, you make such
a lovely image

457
00:17:35,875 --> 00:17:37,291
when peeling vegetables, sister.

458
00:17:37,375 --> 00:17:39,458
- Your bias is so blatant,
it's almost comforting.

459
00:17:39,541 --> 00:17:42,333
I'd like a comment on my work,
too, if you could muster one up.

460
00:17:42,416 --> 00:17:45,333
- How about, "I pity the farmer
who grew those vegetables?"

461
00:17:45,416 --> 00:17:47,708
- Stop being so cruel!
You're breaking my heart.

462
00:17:47,791 --> 00:17:49,791
- You don't know how
to handle a knife, Barusu.

463
00:17:49,875 --> 00:17:52,750
You should hold it still
and simply turn the vegetable.

464
00:17:52,833 --> 00:17:56,125
My best dish is steamed tatoes,
if I do say so myself.

465
00:17:56,208 --> 00:17:58,958
- How can you say that with such
a triumphant look on your face?

466
00:17:59,041 --> 00:18:00,375
[gasps]
Damn it, just watch.

467
00:18:00,458 --> 00:18:02,666
My favorite blade Shooting Star
will show you a thing

468
00:18:02,750 --> 00:18:04,000
or two about slicing!

469
00:18:04,083 --> 00:18:06,333
[screaming]

470
00:18:06,416 --> 00:18:13,458
<i>♪ ♪</i>

471
00:18:15,416 --> 00:18:17,750
[crickets chirping]

472
00:18:17,833 --> 00:18:21,291
- How has Subaru been
since he started working?

473
00:18:21,375 --> 00:18:23,833
Five days have passed
since his arrival.

474
00:18:23,916 --> 00:18:25,750
Shouldn't we be seeing something
by now?

475
00:18:25,833 --> 00:18:28,333
- Cooking, laundry, cleaning--

476
00:18:28,416 --> 00:18:30,250
He's useless at all of them.

477
00:18:30,333 --> 00:18:32,041
- How very harsh of you.

478
00:18:32,125 --> 00:18:35,416
And what are the chances
he's a spy?

479
00:18:35,500 --> 00:18:38,000
- I can't deny
that such potential exists,

480
00:18:38,083 --> 00:18:40,291
but I think the possibility
is slim at best,

481
00:18:40,375 --> 00:18:41,791
'cause for better or for worse--

482
00:18:41,875 --> 00:18:43,708
for worse in this case
in particular--

483
00:18:43,791 --> 00:18:44,916
he's too conspicuous.

484
00:18:45,000 --> 00:18:47,666
- And if he's too conspicuous,
then...

485
00:18:48,333 --> 00:18:50,208
Well, despite the odds
of that possibility,

486
00:18:50,291 --> 00:18:52,541
he certainly is carefree,
isn't he?

487
00:18:53,083 --> 00:18:54,416
Personally as I see it,

488
00:18:54,500 --> 00:18:57,791
it would be wise
to interfere with things.

489
00:18:58,333 --> 00:18:59,750
- They're both only children.

490
00:18:59,833 --> 00:19:02,583
Even if we let them be,
nothing will happen.

491
00:19:07,750 --> 00:19:09,333
- Huh.

492
00:19:09,416 --> 00:19:11,750
- It's not that exciting
to watch, is it?

493
00:19:11,833 --> 00:19:12,750
- You may think that,

494
00:19:12,833 --> 00:19:13,958
but nothing's ever boring

495
00:19:14,041 --> 00:19:15,416
when I'm hanging around you,
Mili.

496
00:19:15,500 --> 00:19:16,583
- That's good to hear,

497
00:19:16,666 --> 00:19:18,333
even if you're only
flattering me.

498
00:19:19,958 --> 00:19:20,916
[chuckles]

499
00:19:21,000 --> 00:19:22,666
- Besides, the two
of us haven't had

