Hi there, Subaru.

752
00:28:38,583 --> 00:28:40,416
Great morning, isn't it?

753
00:28:40,500 --> 00:28:43,750
I really can't thank you enough
for what you did yesterday,

754
00:28:43,833 --> 00:28:46,333
but I'll find a way to somehow.
- I know!

755
00:28:46,416 --> 00:28:47,625
How about you let me
pet your fur

756
00:28:47,708 --> 00:28:48,750
whenever I feel like it?

757
00:28:48,833 --> 00:28:50,125
- Really?
That's all you want?

758
00:28:50,208 --> 00:28:51,541
- [gasps]

759
00:28:51,625 --> 00:28:53,250
[both moaning]

760
00:28:53,333 --> 00:28:54,500
Okay, let's go.

761
00:28:54,583 --> 00:28:56,625
Our time is limited
and our world is grand.

762
00:28:56,708 --> 00:28:59,166
The story of me and Mili
has only just begun.

763
00:28:59,250 --> 00:29:00,375
There's lots to do!

764
00:29:00,458 --> 00:29:01,666
- That's true.

765
00:29:01,750 --> 00:29:03,666
Wait, what did you just say?

766
00:29:03,750 --> 00:29:06,166
Where did the "Mili" come from?

767
00:29:06,250 --> 00:29:08,666
<i>- I don't know whose idea</i>
<i>of a prank this is,</i>

768
00:29:08,750 --> 00:29:10,791
<i>but I'm gonna make you sorry</i>
<i>for all of it.</i>

769
00:29:10,875 --> 00:29:13,250
<i>Don't underestimate</i>
<i>how vindictive I'll be</i>

770
00:29:13,333 --> 00:29:15,500
<i>after the smile that charmed me</i>
<i>that evening.</i>

771
00:29:15,583 --> 00:29:18,250
<i>I'm going to keep my promise</i>
<i>to Mili no matter what.</i>

772
00:29:18,333 --> 00:29:20,208
<i>I'll get past that night.</i>

773
00:29:20,291 --> 00:29:23,333
<i>- Any reward you desire.</i>
<i>Just name it.</i>

774
00:29:23,416 --> 00:29:25,666
- Well, in that case,
I have but one request.

775
00:29:25,750 --> 00:29:27,291
I'm starting
to like this mansion.

776
00:29:27,375 --> 00:29:29,125
Hire me to work here!

777
00:29:29,833 --> 00:29:31,250
- [sneezes]

778
00:29:31,875 --> 00:29:33,458
<i>- It's how these</i>
<i>looping plots work.</i>

779
00:29:33,541 --> 00:29:35,583
<i>All you gotta do is follow</i>
<i>the same path</i>

780
00:29:35,666 --> 00:29:37,250
<i>and you'll end up</i>
<i>in the same place.</i>

781
00:29:38,541 --> 00:29:40,166
- That's too large for you,
Barusu.

782
00:29:40,250 --> 00:29:41,166
- [grunts]

783
00:29:41,250 --> 00:29:42,625
- It seems that nothing here

784
00:29:42,708 --> 00:29:44,500
will fit you
except women's clothes.

785
00:29:44,583 --> 00:29:47,208
Rem, would you please alter
that one for him?

786
00:29:47,291 --> 00:29:48,333
- Yes, of course, sister.

787
00:29:48,416 --> 00:29:50,000
- All right,
take my measurements,

788
00:29:50,083 --> 00:29:51,166
'cause a man like me

789
00:29:51,250 --> 00:29:52,666
can withstand all kinds
of awkwardness.

790
00:29:52,750 --> 00:29:54,750
- We'll measure you
a bit later.

791
00:29:54,833 --> 00:29:57,125
- Eh, huh?
- Now follow me, Barusu.

792
00:29:57,208 --> 00:29:59,541
- Are you gonna show me around
this place or--

793
00:29:59,625 --> 00:30:01,416
- Not right now.
That will also wait.

794
00:30:01,500 --> 00:30:04,291
You're going to be helping me
with my work first.

795
00:30:04,375 --> 00:30:06,166
- Hey, hang on a second!

796
00:30:07,916 --> 00:30:10,708
<i>Retrace the same path</i>
<i>I took yesterday.</i>

797
00:30:10,791 --> 00:30:11,875
<i>Simple.</i>

798
00:30:13,000 --> 00:30:15,208
<i>That's what I meant to do,</i>
<i>but...</i>

799
00:30:15,958 --> 00:30:18,833
This is totally different
from what happened last time.

800
00:30:18,916 --> 00:30:20,416
It's like when you make
a cheat sheet

801
00:30:20,500 --> 00:30:22,791
for a major exam
but when you see the answers,

802
00:30:22,875 --> 00:30:24,500
you realize
it's the wrong subject.

803
00:30:24,583 --> 00:30:25,958
Total waste of effort.
[doors opening]

804
00:30:26,041 --> 00:30:27,041
Hmm?

805
00:30:27,125 --> 00:30:29,000
- Hi, there!
Mind if I join you?

806
00:30:29,083 --> 00:30:30,500
- Yes, I do.

807
00:30:30,583 --> 00:30:32,625
- This facility is part
of my mansion

808
00:30:32,708 --> 00:30:34,291
which makes it my property.

809
00:30:34,375 --> 00:30:36,375
Therefore I'll do with it
as I please.

810
00:30:36,458 --> 00:30:37,916
- Why bother asking permission?

811
00:30:38,000 --> 00:30:39,125
Take a bath if you want to.

812
00:30:39,208 --> 00:30:41,750
- My, what harsh words
from the hired help.

813
00:30:41,833 --> 00:30:43,291
You don't seem to understand.

814
00:30:43,375 --> 00:30:45,375
As we've both made
abundantly clear,

815
00:30:45,458 --> 00:30:47,041
this bath is my property,

816
00:30:47,125 --> 00:30:49,833
but as you are part of my staff,

817
00:30:49,916 --> 00:30:54,750
does it not stand to reason
that you're my property as well?

818
00:30:54,833 --> 00:30:56,875
- Chomp.
- No hesitation at all.

819
00:30:56,958 --> 00:31:00,125
<i>This is turning out different</i>
<i>from what I'd expected, too.</i>

820
00:31:00,750 --> 00:31:02,250
- I don't know
what's bothering you,

821
00:31:02,333 --> 00:31:04,583
but you'll come to discover
that life is full of things

822
00:31:04,666 --> 00:31:06,416
that don't go your way.

823
00:31:07,166 --> 00:31:09,500
Incidentally, what do you think
of my support staff?

824
00:31:09,583 --> 00:31:11,083
Getting along famously, I hope.

825
00:31:11,166 --> 00:31:13,416
- I haven't spoken that much
to Rem at this point,

826
00:31:13,500 --> 00:31:15,083
but I get along
just fine with Ram.

827
00:31:15,166 --> 00:31:16,583
In fact, I think she might

828
00:31:16,666 --> 00:31:18,125
be getting
a little too friendly.

829
00:31:18,208 --> 00:31:20,625
I can't believe she can work
as a maid that way.

830
00:31:20,708 --> 00:31:23,458
- Well, Rem handles the things
Ram is unable to do.

831
00:31:23,541 --> 00:31:25,708
As sisters,
they must help each other.

832
00:31:25,791 --> 00:31:27,541
If you think about it
in that sense,

833
00:31:27,625 --> 00:31:30,416
I believe the two of them
are getting by quite well.

834
00:31:30,500 --> 00:31:32,916
It seems like Ram's the inferior
version of her sister

835
00:31:33,000 --> 00:31:34,791
and all Rem does
is cover for her,

836
00:31:34,875 --> 00:31:37,291
yet they insist Ram is superior
'cause she happens

837
00:31:37,375 --> 00:31:38,541
to be the older one.

838
00:31:38,625 --> 00:31:40,416
It's scary how much nerve
the two of them have.

839
00:31:40,500 --> 00:31:42,541
- While we're on the subject
of nerves,

840
00:31:42,625 --> 00:31:44,916
yours appears
quite impressive as well,

841
00:31:45,000 --> 00:31:46,458
if I do say so.

842
00:31:47,416 --> 00:31:49,083
- Damn, I'm dizzy
from that bath.

843
00:31:49,166 --> 00:31:50,708
Stupid Roswaal.

844
00:31:50,791 --> 00:31:52,541
[screams]

845
00:31:53,125 --> 00:31:55,458
- Would you mind covering up
that sorry thing?

846
00:31:55,541 --> 00:31:57,333
- Hey, what are you doing here?

847
00:31:57,416 --> 00:31:58,791
- I was just waiting to help

848
00:31:58,875 --> 00:32:00,916
Lord Roswaal
put on fresh clothes.

849
00:32:01,000 --> 00:32:02,833
While I'm sure you
were looking forward to it,

850
00:32:02,916 --> 00:32:04,958
I'm sorry to say that
I finished my bath,

851
00:32:05,041 --> 00:32:06,791
so I won't be changing.
- As if!

852
00:32:06,875 --> 00:32:08,083
I wasn't thinking
about that at all!

853
00:32:08,166 --> 00:32:10,166
On top of that,
you spoil him too much.

854
00:32:10,250 --> 00:32:12,125
Let him dress himself!
- Enough.

855
00:32:12,208 --> 00:32:14,791
I will not condone disrespect
toward Lord Roswaal.

856
00:32:14,875 --> 00:32:17,291
Next time I will use
a more forceful approach.

857
00:32:17,375 --> 00:32:19,500
- Easy.
Don't stir the hornet's nest.

858
00:32:19,583 --> 00:32:22,333
- By the way, Barusu,
do you have plans after this?

859
00:32:22,416 --> 00:32:24,625
- No, not really.
I'm just going to sleep.

860
00:32:24,708 --> 00:32:26,291
- Then please wait
in your room for me.

861
00:32:26,375 --> 00:32:27,833
I'll come by later.

862
00:32:28,708 --> 00:32:29,791
- Huh?

863
00:32:29,875 --> 00:32:31,458
Easy.
She didn't mean anything by it.

864
00:32:31,541 --> 00:32:33,500
Clear your mind.
Mili's the only one for you.

865
00:32:33,583 --> 00:32:34,666
Calm down.
Calm down!

866
00:32:34,750 --> 00:32:37,166
One smiling Mili.
Two smiling Milis.

867
00:32:37,250 --> 00:32:38,958
Three smiling Milis.

868
00:32:39,041 --> 00:32:42,291
Am I in Heaven?
- You're far too noisy, Barusu.

869
00:32:42,375 --> 00:32:44,125
It's nighttime.
You need to be quiet now.

870
00:32:44,208 --> 00:32:45,500
- [whimpers]

871
00:32:46,416 --> 00:32:48,625
- Barusu, come over here.

872
00:32:48,708 --> 00:32:50,541
- Wait, my heart's already
set on someone

873
00:32:50,625 --> 00:32:52,125
and her name is Mili!

874
00:32:52,208 --> 00:32:53,583
- What are you talking about?

875
00:32:53,666 --> 00:32:55,708
I'm telling you that you need
to sit over here

876
00:32:55,791 --> 00:32:57,208
so I can teach you how
to read and write.

877
00:32:57,291 --> 00:32:58,791
- That's what you wanted?

878
00:32:59,333 --> 00:33:00,875
So where's this coming from?

879
00:33:00,958 --> 00:33:02,666
- I could tell by watching you

880
00:33:02,750 --> 00:33:04,375
that you're
completely illiterate.

881
00:33:04,458 --> 00:33:07,500
If you can't read or write,
then I can't send you shopping.

882
00:33:07,583 --> 00:33:09,791
It also means you can't
take down orders.

883
00:33:09,875 --> 00:33:12,708
We'll start with
some children's fairy tales.

884
00:33:12,791 --> 00:33:13,833
Beginning tonight,

885
00:33:13,916 --> 00:33:15,708
I'll help you study
every evening.

886
00:33:15,791 --> 00:33:18,458
- Thanks, but why are you being
so nice to me?

887
00:33:18,541 --> 00:33:20,041
- Well, why do you think?

888
00:33:20,125 --> 00:33:22,166
So I can--no, wait.

889
00:33:22,250 --> 00:33:24,916
It makes things easier for me.
- You're correcting yourself?

890
00:33:25,000 --> 00:33:26,416
You're never out of character.

891
00:33:26,500 --> 00:33:27,791
- It's rather obvious.

892
00:33:27,875 --> 00:33:30,125
The more you're able to do
and handle on your own,

893
00:33:30,208 --> 00:33:31,958
the less I have
to do around here,

894
00:33:32,041 --> 00:33:33,375
and when I have less to do,

895
00:33:33,458 --> 00:33:35,583
that means Rem's workload
is lighter also.

896
00:33:35,666 --> 00:33:37,666
So it's a total win-win.
- Look, I get it,

897
00:33:37,750 --> 00:33:40,250
but that leaves me
with piles of work, though!

898
00:33:40,333 --> 00:33:42,708
- We'll start
with the basic i-glyphs.

899
00:33:42,791 --> 00:33:44,708
After that, we'll move on
to ro-glyphs

900
00:33:44,791 --> 00:33:45,875
and ha-glyphs.

901
00:33:45,958 --> 00:33:47,375
- There are three
different types?

902
00:33:47,458 --> 00:33:49,083
Just hearing that
is depressing.

903
00:33:49,166 --> 00:33:51,833
- You don't have time to waste
on silly doodles.

904
00:33:51,916 --> 00:33:54,833
We have an early start tomorrow
so we're short on time.

905
00:33:54,916 --> 00:33:56,291
I'm sleepy, too.

906
00:33:56,375 --> 00:33:58,666
- You know, can't say I dislike
how you manage to slip in

907
00:33:58,750 --> 00:34:00,583
your own feelings about this
at the end of that thought.

908
00:34:00,666 --> 00:34:02,166
- In my own humble opinion,

909
00:34:02,250 --> 00:34:04,500
I believe honesty
is my most charming feature.

910
00:34:04,583 --> 00:34:06,250
Now then,
let's get started.

911
00:34:09,416 --> 00:34:10,708
- So monotonous,

912
00:34:10,791 --> 00:34:12,791
I feel a Gestaltzerfall
phenomenon coming on.

913
00:34:13,041 --> 00:34:15,541
But still, even if you did
teach me to read and write

914
00:34:15,625 --> 00:34:18,166
just to make your life easier,
it made me happy.

915
00:34:18,541 --> 00:34:20,416
Honestly, I was beginning
to get the feeling

916
00:34:20,500 --> 00:34:22,125
you just didn't like me
that much,

917
00:34:22,208 --> 00:34:24,250
and I'll probably cause
even more problems for you

918
00:34:24,333 --> 00:34:26,583
down the line,
but I'll try to become useful

919
00:34:26,666 --> 00:34:30,750
as soon as I...
- [breathing heavily]

920
00:34:30,833 --> 00:34:31,916
- [grunts]

921
00:34:35,708 --> 00:34:36,791
- Oh, wow.

922
00:34:36,875 --> 00:34:38,416
It actually turned out perfect.

923
00:34:38,500 --> 00:34:40,166
Guess my sewing skills

924
00:34:40,250 --> 00:34:42,125
aren't gonna be needed
this time around, huh?

925
00:34:42,208 --> 00:34:43,708
- Your sewing skills?

926
00:34:43,791 --> 00:34:45,083
If you excel at it,

927
00:34:45,166 --> 00:34:46,583
I assume you enjoy it, then?

928
00:34:46,666 --> 00:34:47,791
- Yeah, kinda.

929
00:34:47,875 --> 00:34:49,791
By the way,
it looks like Ros and Mili

930
00:34:49,875 --> 00:34:51,500
have quite a few outfits
to choose from,

931
00:34:51,583 --> 00:34:53,875
but I don't really see any
for you or Ram.

932
00:34:53,958 --> 00:34:55,708
Want me to sew some for you?

933
00:34:55,791 --> 00:34:57,083
I'll take your measurements.

934
00:34:57,166 --> 00:34:58,416
- That's not necessary.

935
00:34:58,500 --> 00:35:00,791
The uniforms my sister
and I wear daily

936
00:35:00,875 --> 00:35:02,666
are all that we need.
- Seriously?

937
00:35:02,750 --> 00:35:05,125
How can you have nothing
but those uniforms?

938
00:35:05,208 --> 00:35:06,583
You own no other clothes?

939
00:35:06,666 --> 00:35:09,000
- It makes things much easier
when there are guests here

940
00:35:09,083 --> 00:35:12,125
in the mansion or when we're
with Lord Roswaal on business.

941
00:35:12,208 --> 00:35:14,583
Doing so eliminates the need
to explain our place

942
00:35:14,666 --> 00:35:16,750
in the hierarchy which makes it
very logical.

943
00:35:16,833 --> 00:35:19,500
- Well, I'm not talking
about being logical here.

944
00:35:19,583 --> 00:35:22,083
What I'm trying to say is that
a couple of cute girls like you

945
00:35:22,166 --> 00:35:23,958
and your sister ought
to dress up and look nice

946
00:35:24,041 --> 00:35:25,583
both for yourselves
and other people, you know?

947
00:35:25,666 --> 00:35:28,125
- As far as that goes,
my sister's one thing,

948
00:35:28,208 --> 00:35:30,125
but no one would be happy
to see me dress up.

949
00:35:30,208 --> 00:35:32,041
- You're wrong there.
I sure would.

950
00:35:32,125 --> 00:35:33,375
- Well, even if that's true,

951
00:35:33,458 --> 00:35:35,083
what good would come
of making you happy?

952
00:35:35,166 --> 00:35:37,333
- I might take a little
more pride in my work here,

953
00:35:37,416 --> 00:35:38,958
which could boost
my productivity.

954
00:35:39,041 --> 00:35:41,333
- I've no idea what would
make you say such a thing.

955
00:35:41,416 --> 00:35:42,958
That mindset makes no sense.

956
00:35:43,041 --> 00:35:44,791
- I'd also look forward
to seeing the differences

957
00:35:44,875 --> 00:35:46,166
in the clothing
you'd each choose.

958
00:35:46,250 --> 00:35:47,916
Who'd be classy,
who'd be risque.

959
00:35:48,000 --> 00:35:49,125
- That's irrelevant.

960
00:35:49,208 --> 00:35:51,000
Does my looking the same
as my sister

961
00:35:51,083 --> 00:35:53,208
inconvenience you somehow?

962
00:35:53,833 --> 00:35:56,416
- If you ask me, you love
your sister way too much.

963
00:35:56,500 --> 00:35:58,041
[slicing]
[shouts]

964
00:35:58,125 --> 00:36:00,708
- You've no idea how to properly
handle a knife, Barusu.

965
00:36:00,791 --> 00:36:02,333
- I know what I'm doing.

966
00:36:02,416 --> 00:36:04,875
You hold the knife still
and turn the food item, right?

967
00:36:04,958 --> 00:36:06,875
[pot bubbling]

968
00:36:06,958 --> 00:36:08,125
[grunts]

969
00:36:08,208 --> 00:36:09,625
It's kind of embarrassing

970
00:36:09,708 --> 00:36:11,291
when you stare
at me so intently.

971
00:36:11,375 --> 00:36:13,083
<i>[quirky music]</i>

972
00:36:13,166 --> 00:36:14,791
Huh?
- Your unsightly appearance

973
00:36:14,875 --> 00:36:16,500
stands out
and makes you an eyesore.

974
00:36:16,583 --> 00:36:18,000
Especially your hair.

975
00:36:18,083 --> 00:36:19,416
It's incredibly unrefined.

976
00:36:19,500 --> 00:36:21,208
- It really looks that bad?

977
00:36:21,291 --> 00:36:22,416
I thought I did
a pretty good job

978
00:36:22,500 --> 00:36:24,375
of cutting it by myself.

979
00:36:24,833 --> 00:36:25,958
<i>- By the way,</i>

980
00:36:26,041 --> 00:36:27,500
<i>Rem takes care</i>
<i>of everyone's hair</i>

981
00:36:27,583 --> 00:36:29,041
<i>in this mansion.</i>

982
00:36:29,125 --> 00:36:31,458
<i>She styles mine and dresses me</i>
<i>every morning as well.</i>

983
00:36:31,541 --> 00:36:33,083
<i>Nice of her,</i>
<i>don't you think?</i>

984
00:36:33,166 --> 00:36:35,500
<i>- You should try to contribute</i>
<i>a little more around here.</i>

985
00:36:35,583 --> 00:36:41,541
<i>♪ ♪</i>

986
00:36:41,625 --> 00:36:43,750
- Hey, Rem.
If you like,

987
00:36:43,833 --> 00:36:45,958
feel free to tidy up
Barusu's hair a little.

988
00:36:46,041 --> 00:36:47,250
- Pardon me?

989
00:36:47,333 --> 00:36:48,375
- Whoa, whoa, whoa!

990
00:36:48,458 --> 00:36:49,750
Having a girl mess with my hair

991
00:36:49,833 --> 00:36:51,041
will get me all worked up!

992
00:36:51,125 --> 00:36:52,583
- The reason you keep looking
at Barusu

993
